defaultThe evidence presented relates to scheduled pubic bus services and therefore omits the Committee’s points 4 and 5 as these concern community transport, taxis and demand responsive services outside the scope of the four parish surveys.
defaultHexham is the princip
defaultal market town in West Northumberland and serves a large sparsely populated rural hinterland. 
defaultHexham itself has good bus and rail links to Newcastle, Gateshead and Carlisle but the smaller towns and villages which Hexham serves depend on supported bus serv
defaultices and community transport. Because of the long distances involved the cost per passenger is relatively high
default, communities which Hexham serves include Kielder 38 miles, Bellingham 18 miles, and Allendale 11 miles. 
