defaultto include Hexham’s superm
defaultarkets. Higher passenger numbers should help to make the services more economically viable. However the County Council is having to make cuts to its supported bus services budget while at the same time operators costs are rising (and they are having to abs
defaultorb the 20% reduction in the BOSG). 
defaultThe result is almost certain to be a reduction in the services provided to this very rural area leading to 
default(a) more car dependence and 
default(b) more, mostly older people, becoming isolated. 
default(c) reduced
default access to the countryside for people living in Hexham itself. 
defaultThese are issues which concern Hexham as a traditional market town serving a large rural hinterland. 
